Let's calculate the present value of investment X at a 5% discount rate. Since investment X has an eight-year team, we will calculate the present value for each year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value} &=\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 + .05\right)^{1}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 + .05\right)^{2}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 +.05\right)^{3}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 + .05\right)^{4}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 +.05\right)^{5}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 + .05\right)^{6}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 +.05\right)^{7}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 + .05\right)^{8}}
\\[10pt]
&=\$4,000+\$3,809.52+\$3,628.12+\$3,455.35 
+\$3,290.81+\$3,134.10+\$2,984.86 +\$2,842.73 
\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\$27,145.49}
\end{aligned}$$

Hence, the present value of investment X at a 5% discount rate is $27,145.49.

Next, let's compute the present value of investment Y using the 5% discount rate.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value} &=\dfrac{\$6,100}{\left(1 + .05\right)^{1}}+\dfrac{\$6,100}{\left(1 + .05\right)^{2}}+\dfrac{\$6,100}{\left(1 +.05\right)^{3}}+\dfrac{\$6,100}{\left(1 + .05\right)^{4}}+\dfrac{\$6,100}{\left(1 +.05\right)^{5}}
\\[10pt]
&=\$5,809.52+\$5,532.88+\$5,269.41 +\$5,018.49 +\$4,779.51 
\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\$26,409.81}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, the present value of investment Y at a 5% discount rate is $26,409.81.

First, let's determine the present value of investment X using the discount rate of 15%.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value} &=\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 + .15\right)^{1}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 + .15\right)^{2}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 +.15\right)^{3}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 + .15\right)^{4}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 +.15\right)^{5}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 + .15\right)^{6}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 +.15\right)^{7}}+\dfrac{\$4,200}{\left(1 + .15\right)^{8}}
\\[10pt]
&=\$3,652.17+\$3,175.80+\$2,761.57+\$2,401.36
+\$2,088.14+\$1,815.78+\$1,578.94+\$1,372.99
\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\$18,846.75}
\end{aligned}$$

As can be seen in our calculation, the present value of investment X at a 15% rate is $18,846.75.

Next, let's calculate the present value of investment Y if the discount rate is 15%.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value} &=\dfrac{\$6,100}{\left(1 + .15\right)^{1}}+\dfrac{\$6,100}{\left(1 + .15\right)^{2}}+\dfrac{\$6,100}{\left(1 +.15\right)^{3}}+\dfrac{\$6,100}{\left(1 + .15\right)^{4}}+\dfrac{\$6,100}{\left(1 +.15\right)^{5}}
\\[10pt]
&=\$5,304.35 +\$4,612.48+\$4,010.85+\$3,487.69 +\$3,032.78 
\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\$20,448.15}
\end{aligned}$$

Our calculation shows that the investment's present value if the discount rate is 15% is $20,448.15.
